Credit Card Fraud Detection

Context:

The datasets contains transactions made by credit cards in September 2013 by european cardholders.
This dataset presents transactions that occurred in two days, where we have 492 frauds out of 284,807 transactions.
The financial companies need to recognize fraudulent credit card transactions to protect their customers.


Criteria for success:
Flagging a fraudulent transaction will protect the customers from being charged for the items that they did not purchase

Scope of solution space
An efficient model to flag out the fraudulent transactions and stopping the transaction from happening without a user confirmation will
increase security

Constraints:
 The dataset is highly unbalanced, the positive class (frauds) account for 0.172% of all transactions

StakeHolders
Bank Manager,
customers of credit cards


Key DataSources:
single CSV file from kaggle https://www.kaggle.com/mlg-ulb/creditcardfraud
